# User-Level Workspace Integration in pi-web

Based on your feedback, this updated plan implements a **persistent, per-user workspace** rather than a session-bound one. The workspace resides at `/tmp/pi-web-users/{username}/workspace` and persists across sessions, allowing users to clone repositories, create folders, edit files, and have the agent operate on them continuously.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Key Architecture Decisions:**
> 1. **Per-User Workspace Root:** All file tree and CRUD operations will operate on `/tmp/pi-web-users/{username}/workspace`.
> 2. **Agent Execution Context:** The agent's session will execute commands and tools inside the user's workspace directory (`cwd: workspaceDir`), while its conversation state (`.jsonl` files) will remain session-specific inside `/tmp/pi-web-users/{username}/sessions/{sessionId}`.
> 3. **Compatibility fallback:** Existing image grid / file preview requests pointing to `/api/sessions/:sessionId/files/*` will check the session directory first, and fall back to searching in the user's workspace directory, preventing any broken links.
> 4. **Collapsible Workspace Panel:** Toggleable workspace panel on the right side of the chat area on desktop, collapsing to an overlay drawer on mobile devices.

## Proposed Changes

